commitResults.messageTitle: ApunableBot.java: Handle incorrect inputs entered by the user
ApunableBot.java: Add delete feature and modularize the code
commitResults.messageBody:
User can input "delete <index>" to delete the task.

The switch in main function is too long, make it difficult to add new
features, need to abstract away some part of it.

Add helper functions to abstract away the essential part of switch, can
shorten the code and make it easier to maintain.

commitResults.messageTitle: src/main/java: Enable saving tasklist into file after exit
src\main\java: Reorganize into classes/objects for clearer workflow
commitResults.messageBody:
The code is reorganized for clearer workflow, easier for future
development and for others to understand the code.

The code is split into:
1. `utils` folder
- `DataSaver`: load and save tasklist from and to hardisk
- `InputProcessor`: handle user input and turn into standard format
- `CommandHandler`: handle various commands(list, mark, unmark etc.)

1. `tasks` folder
- store different type of tasks(`todo`, `event`, `deadline`)

1. `types` folder
- important types that will be used frequently, such as
  - `CommandEnum`: enum that store types of available commands
  - `FormattedInput`: datatype that user input will be refactored into
